Usage: add_gui_text [-help]
                    [-alignment {upperLeft centerLeft lowerLeft upperCenter centerCenter lowerCenter upperRight centerRight lowerRight}]
                    -label <text> -layer <layerName> {-box {x1 y1 x2 y2} | {{-height <height> | -fixed_height <fixHeight> } -pt {x y} [-orient <dir>]}} [ -box {x1 y1 x2 y2} [-no_bbox ] ]

-help                         # Prints out the command usage
-alignment {upperLeft centerLeft lowerLeft upperCenter centerCenter lowerCenter upperRight centerRight lowerRight}
                              # specify the alignment of the font (enum, optional)
-box {x1 y1 x2 y2}            # Coordinates of the lower-left and upper-right
                              # points of the rectangle (values are in microns)
                              # (box, optional)
-fixed_height <fixHeight>     # The height in pixels (int, optional)
-height <height>              # The height in microns (float, optional)
-label <text>                 # The text string (string, required)
-layer <layerName>            # GUI layer name to use or create for the text.
                              # If the specified layer does not exist, it will
                              # be automatically created. (string, required)
-no_bbox                      # Not draw bounding box when -box option is
                              # sepcified (bool, required)
-orient <dir>                 # The dir contains MX MX90 MY MY90 R0 R90 R180
                              # R270 (string, optional)
-pt {x y}                     # The origin coordinate of the text (values are
                              # in microns) (point, optional)